[h1]Return[/h1]

A function can return a value using the [b]return [/b]statement.
Return stops the function's execution, and sends the value back to the calling code.
[b]For example: [/b][code format="php" codeId="492"]function mult($num1, $num2) {
  $res = $num1 * $num2;
  [b]return[/b] $res;
}

echo mult(8, 3);
// Outputs 24[/code]
[note]Leaving out the return results in a [b]NULL[/b] value being returned.
A function cannot return multiple values, but returning an [b]array[/b] will produce similar results.[/note]
